Jim Gilbert wrote:

&gt;Rich,
&gt;Musashino.  The myoga and matsukawabishi don&#39;t normally have anything to do with the musashino design.  They&#39;re rather common decorative devices for &quot;making&quot; hitsuana and were probably originally introduced as mon but then became part of the tsuba designer&#39;s vocabulary.
&gt;
&gt;You&#39;re probably right about it being Owari.  There are Owari guards with very Akasaka-esq designs that predate Akasaka.  The seppa dai is quite broad at both the top and bottom.  The rim isn&#39;t very rounded.  The texture of the metal and the carving don&#39;t really fit Akasaka.  The hitsuana treatment would be rather unusual for Akasaka.  Looks like a nice guard.
&gt;
&gt;Jim  
&gt;
